EPISODE 8
"ADDICTIVE LOVE" – PYEONGYANG COLD NOODLES

9
00:00:31,164 --> 00:00:33,901
Is this a tourist spot?

10
00:00:33,967 --> 00:00:36,603
No, surprisingly,
this is actually the central area.

11
00:00:36,703 --> 00:00:39,172
-Do you see the N Seoul Tower behind us?
-Yes.

12
00:00:39,873 --> 00:00:41,775
It used to be called Namsan Tower.

13
00:00:41,909 --> 00:00:43,911
It’s now called N Seoul Tower,
though the rename…

14
00:00:43,977 --> 00:00:45,212
-Yes.
-…wasn’t recent.

15
00:00:45,279 --> 00:00:47,681
-N Seoul Tower? Really?
-Yes. N Seoul Tower.

16
00:00:47,748 --> 00:00:49,349
-You can see the night view…
-Yes.

17
00:00:49,416 --> 00:00:53,220
-…and that round part rotates.
-Wow.

18
00:00:53,854 --> 00:00:56,657
So guys take their girlfriends there.

19
00:00:56,723 --> 00:00:58,225
-I haven’t, though.
-It's a date spot?

20
00:00:58,292 --> 00:00:59,159
-Yes.
-Oh…

21
00:00:59,226 --> 00:01:01,495
Don't be so sad. I'll go with you.

22
00:01:01,562 --> 00:01:03,330
-Really?
-Yes.

23
00:01:03,463 --> 00:01:05,566
-I'll have to leave early, though.
-That's fine.

24
00:01:07,334 --> 00:01:10,938
-My parents came here…
-Yes.

25
00:01:11,004 --> 00:01:13,440
-…when they used to date.
-Oh.

26
00:01:13,507 --> 00:01:18,412
Then it's a place that's been around
since your parents' youth.

27
00:01:18,478 --> 00:01:21,081
Yes, I used to eat there when I was young.

28
00:01:21,148 --> 00:01:22,649
I see.

29
00:01:22,783 --> 00:01:25,185
-It has a very mild flavor…
-Yes.

30
00:01:25,252 --> 00:01:27,487
-…so even kids like it.
-Is that so?

31
00:01:27,588 --> 00:01:29,523
So Koreans eat cold noodles

32
00:01:29,590 --> 00:01:32,159
even in the winter.

33
00:01:32,292 --> 00:01:34,094
-It's served in cold broth.
-Yes.

34
00:01:34,161 --> 00:01:37,097
-So it might seem more suitable in summer.
-Yes.

35
00:01:37,197 --> 00:01:40,734
But some say that it tastes
way better in winter.

36
00:01:40,801 --> 00:01:42,135
Is that so?

37
00:01:42,202 --> 00:01:44,805
-Shall we go in?
-I'd like to know why.

38
00:01:44,938 --> 00:01:47,174
-This place looks cool.
-Yes.

39
00:01:47,274 --> 00:01:49,476
-It's pretty old.
-It has a history.

40
00:01:49,576 --> 00:01:50,978
-Shall we go in?
-Let's go.

41
00:01:53,680 --> 00:01:55,349
-Hello.
-You can go to the second floor.

42
00:01:55,415 --> 00:01:57,784
-Hello.
-Hello.

43
00:01:57,851 --> 00:01:59,553
Everyone seems to be enjoying it.

44
00:02:01,488 --> 00:02:03,590
-Here?
-Yes. Have a seat.

45
00:02:05,025 --> 00:02:07,394
Even at this time of day,
downstairs is full

46
00:02:07,527 --> 00:02:09,930
of people eating cold noodles.

47
00:02:09,997 --> 00:02:12,799
You have to wait in line
for at least 30 minutes during the summer.

48
00:02:12,866 --> 00:02:14,401
Oh…

49
00:02:14,534 --> 00:02:16,103
-Shall we order?
-Yes.

50
00:02:16,203 --> 00:02:18,772
-We'll have some jeyuk…
-Yes.

51
00:02:18,839 --> 00:02:21,208
-…and some dumplings and chat a bit.
-Yes.

52
00:02:21,274 --> 00:02:22,776
-Then we'll order cold noodles.
-Okay.

53
00:02:22,843 --> 00:02:24,711
DUMPLINGS: 15,000 WON
JEYUK: 30,000 WON

54
00:02:24,811 --> 00:02:26,680
-We'll have one jeyuk.
-Yes.

55
00:02:26,747 --> 00:02:28,615
-Also one dish of dumplings.
-Okay.

56
00:02:30,050 --> 00:02:33,353
-Do you need non-alcoholic beer?
-Soju is fine.

57
00:02:33,420 --> 00:02:35,389
-Really? Okay.
-Yes. Soju.

58
00:02:35,522 --> 00:02:38,358
-One bottle of soju, please.
-Sure.

59
00:02:38,525 --> 00:02:39,760
-Thank you.
-Hello.

60
00:02:39,826 --> 00:02:41,028
-Hello.
-Hello.

61
00:02:41,361 --> 00:02:42,696
Here.

62
00:02:43,830 --> 00:02:46,033
-Wow, what's this?
-Here's your noodle water.

63
00:02:46,099 --> 00:02:48,602
It’s the water used to boil the noodles.

64
00:02:48,669 --> 00:02:50,237
-Like sobayu?
-Yes.

65
00:02:50,303 --> 00:02:52,139
-They give it to you at the start?
-Yes.

66
00:02:52,639 --> 00:02:57,010
SOBAYU: WATER USED TO BOIL SOBA NOODLES
IT'S USUALLY SERVED AFTER THE MEAL

67
00:02:57,544 --> 00:02:59,112
-It's warm.
-That's good.

68
00:02:59,179 --> 00:03:00,881
-Let's drink.
-It's perfect for cold weather.

69
00:03:00,947 --> 00:03:02,215
Thank you.

70
00:03:10,757 --> 00:03:12,993
This tastes interesting.

71
00:03:13,126 --> 00:03:16,630
-You've never had it in Korea, right?
-Right, it's my first time.

72
00:03:16,697 --> 00:03:20,667
Fascinating. Shall we have soju next?

73
00:03:22,302 --> 00:03:23,270
Thank you.

74
00:03:23,403 --> 00:03:25,639
-Don't drink too much.
-I won't.

75
00:03:25,739 --> 00:03:27,441
-Just lick it.
-I will.

76
00:03:27,507 --> 00:03:28,975
Thank you.

77
00:03:30,610 --> 00:03:33,447
-So your parents were regulars here?
-Yes.

78
00:03:33,580 --> 00:03:35,582
So, since elementary school, I've had…

79
00:03:35,682 --> 00:03:37,617
-You had cold noodles?
-Yes.

80
00:03:37,751 --> 00:03:41,021
-Back in the day, the owner…
-Yes.

81
00:03:41,088 --> 00:03:43,857
-…always sat at the very back.
-Yes.

82
00:03:43,957 --> 00:03:45,959
-At the back?
-He sat there and read the newspaper.

83
00:03:46,026 --> 00:03:48,695
-Even when people were lined up waiting.
-Is that so?

84
00:03:48,829 --> 00:03:51,965
Back then, the cold noodles cost
a few hundred won.

85
00:03:52,065 --> 00:03:54,267
-It was cheap?
-Yes, the price…

86
00:03:54,334 --> 00:03:55,702
My father told me this.

87
00:03:55,836 --> 00:03:57,904
-There used to be something called Minja.
-Minja?

88
00:03:57,971 --> 00:03:59,606
If you order Minja, you get

89
00:03:59,706 --> 00:04:01,808
-twice the noodles with no toppings.
-Yes.

90
00:04:01,942 --> 00:04:04,177
-Oh…
-You'd only get noodles and broth.

91
00:04:04,511 --> 00:04:09,249
Koreans usually greeted others
by asking if they had eaten,

92
00:04:09,382 --> 00:04:11,184
-instead of saying "Hello."
-I see.

93
00:04:11,284 --> 00:04:12,352
It was like that

94
00:04:12,419 --> 00:04:15,822
-around 40 to 50 years ago.
-Yes.

95
00:04:15,922 --> 00:04:21,394
So I’d just get extra noodles.

96
00:04:21,495 --> 00:04:24,030
-Oh…
-No meat and no eggs.

97
00:04:24,097 --> 00:04:26,800
-I just wanted more noodles.
-I see.

98
00:04:26,933 --> 00:04:28,835
You must’ve grown up thinking this was

99
00:04:28,935 --> 00:04:31,104
what cold noodles are supposed to be.

100
00:04:31,238 --> 00:04:33,874
-I tried everything here.
-When you were young?

101
00:04:33,940 --> 00:04:36,309
-Yes, this was my main spot…
-Yes.

102
00:04:36,376 --> 00:04:38,145
-…so when you first…
-Yes.

103
00:04:38,278 --> 00:04:40,147
-…try cold noodles here…
-Yes.

104
00:04:40,213 --> 00:04:41,915
-…it naturally tastes good to you.
-I get it.

105
00:04:42,015 --> 00:04:44,184
-But Pyeongyang cold noodles…
-Yes.

106
00:04:44,317 --> 00:04:45,886
-…all taste different.
-Is that so?

107
00:04:46,019 --> 00:04:48,622
-Hold on. I'm sorry.
-Yes?

108
00:04:48,688 --> 00:04:50,891
But to Japanese people,

109
00:04:51,024 --> 00:04:52,392
cold noodles are a dish you have

110
00:04:52,459 --> 00:04:54,494
-at the end of a yakiniku meal.
-Right.

111
00:04:54,561 --> 00:04:55,962
So, "Do you want bibimbap?"

112
00:04:56,029 --> 00:04:58,198
-"Or gukbap? Cold noodles?"
-Yes.

113
00:04:58,331 --> 00:05:01,434
-"Or yukgaejang?"
-Yes. It's one of those.

114
00:05:01,501 --> 00:05:05,172
I'm sorry, but all cold noodles
tasted the same for me.

115
00:05:05,238 --> 00:05:07,107
I hope that changes for you today.

116
00:05:07,207 --> 00:05:08,775
-Today…
-Is the broth different?

117
00:05:08,909 --> 00:05:10,110
It is different.

118
00:05:10,210 --> 00:05:14,347
-I heard they mix meat broth…
-Yes.

119
00:05:14,414 --> 00:05:17,684
-…and dongchimi broth.
-I see.

120
00:05:17,818 --> 00:05:20,954
There are a lot
of cold noodle places these days.

121
00:05:21,021 --> 00:05:23,089
-They serve really good cold noodles.
-Yes.

122
00:05:23,156 --> 00:05:24,958
But I think this place is the best.

123
00:05:25,058 --> 00:05:27,961
-Is that so?
-It is addicting.

124
00:05:28,061 --> 00:05:30,263
-I wonder why.
-Your first experience is important.

125
00:05:30,330 --> 00:05:33,600
-I see.
-That's why I had to bring you here.

126
00:05:33,667 --> 00:05:35,135
-Amazing.
-Yes.

127
00:05:35,202 --> 00:05:36,770
I'm sorry.

128
00:05:36,937 --> 00:05:39,372
-Japanese people don't know much about it.
-Good.

129
00:05:39,472 --> 00:05:42,042
I'm drooling as we're talking about it.

130
00:05:42,108 --> 00:05:43,577
Really? Because you want to eat it?

131
00:05:43,643 --> 00:05:44,778
-Like a dog.
-Like a dog.

132
00:05:45,645 --> 00:05:46,646
Right.

133
00:05:46,746 --> 00:05:47,914
It's here!

134
00:05:49,482 --> 00:05:50,750
-It's here.
-Thank you.

135
00:05:50,817 --> 00:05:51,751
-Thank you.
-Sure.

136
00:05:55,255 --> 00:05:59,559
DUMPLINGS: 15,000 WON
APPROXIMATELY 1,500 YEN

137
00:05:59,693 --> 00:06:01,228
-What is this?
-Here.

138
00:06:01,294 --> 00:06:02,662
-This is jeyuk.
-I see.

139
00:06:02,796 --> 00:06:03,797
Oh…

140
00:06:04,664 --> 00:06:09,102
JEYUK: 30,000 WON
APPROXIMATELY 3,000 YEN

141
00:06:09,236 --> 00:06:11,972
-Is it steamed pork?
-It's similar to bossam.

142
00:06:12,038 --> 00:06:14,040
-Yes.
-They boil the pork

143
00:06:14,107 --> 00:06:17,377
then press it down with something heavy.

144
00:06:17,444 --> 00:06:20,347
-The oil gets released, making it chewy.
-I see.

145
00:06:20,413 --> 00:06:21,848
Oh…

146
00:06:21,948 --> 00:06:24,084
-Shall we have jeyuk first?
-Shall we? Okay.

147
00:06:24,150 --> 00:06:26,419
You dip it in the sauce.
You can add mustard

148
00:06:26,519 --> 00:06:28,255
if you like.

149
00:06:28,321 --> 00:06:29,756
-Here?
-Would you like some?

150
00:06:29,823 --> 00:06:31,791
-Yes, I'll try some.
-Okay.

151
00:06:33,493 --> 00:06:37,497
You always get sauce with Korean dishes.

152
00:06:37,564 --> 00:06:39,232
-Like this.
-Yes.

153
00:06:39,366 --> 00:06:42,636
-When I make bossam…
-Yes.

154
00:06:42,702 --> 00:06:46,306
-…in Tokyo, Japan…
-Yes.

155
00:06:46,406 --> 00:06:48,041
…I dip it in vinegar and mustard.

156
00:06:48,475 --> 00:06:50,510
-Really?
-Yes. That's how I like it.

157
00:06:51,011 --> 00:06:52,913
-Thank you for the food.
-That's nice. Enjoy.

158
00:07:03,790 --> 00:07:05,325
-The texture is nice, right?
-It's good.

159
00:07:06,559 --> 00:07:09,763
Bossam has a very soft texture.

160
00:07:09,863 --> 00:07:14,000
This feels like it’s been pressed
with a weight to drain the oil.

161
00:07:14,100 --> 00:07:17,671
-Almost like it’s been pickled.
-That’s why they say

162
00:07:17,737 --> 00:07:19,706
-the flavor becomes more concentrated.
-Yes.

163
00:07:19,873 --> 00:07:22,375
-Applying pressure…
-Yes.

164
00:07:22,442 --> 00:07:23,743
-…and letting it sit…
-Yes.

165
00:07:23,843 --> 00:07:25,946
-…gives it more bounce…
-Right.

166
00:07:26,012 --> 00:07:29,849
-…and enhances the savory flavor.
-Yes.

167
00:07:30,383 --> 00:07:31,418
Oh…

168
00:07:32,218 --> 00:07:34,387
-Can I try vinegar and mustard?
-I want to try too.

169
00:07:35,855 --> 00:07:37,290
I've never tried that combination.

170
00:07:37,424 --> 00:07:40,226
I think vinegar and mustard will be good.

171
00:07:40,293 --> 00:07:42,362
This isn’t really
a Japanese palate thing, right?

172
00:07:42,429 --> 00:07:44,397
-It's just how you like it, right?
-Yes.

173
00:07:44,464 --> 00:07:45,465
I see.

174
00:07:47,600 --> 00:07:50,737
BIG BRO MATJJIGAE'S SAUCE RECOMMENDATION
VINEGAR AND MUSTARD

175
00:07:52,906 --> 00:07:55,241
Try it. It's good.

176
00:07:55,976 --> 00:07:57,243
I've never tried it like this.

177
00:08:02,716 --> 00:08:04,417
-How is it?
-Nice.

178
00:08:04,584 --> 00:08:06,052
-It's good, right?
-Yes.

179
00:08:06,953 --> 00:08:08,355
This is good.

180
00:08:08,421 --> 00:08:09,990
Because the meat can be oily.

181
00:08:10,090 --> 00:08:14,194
-The oily flavor becomes mild.
-Yes.

182
00:08:16,196 --> 00:08:19,132
-I eat dumplings like this too.
-I see.

183
00:08:21,468 --> 00:08:23,236
This kimchi is mild.

184
00:08:27,674 --> 00:08:31,778
-It's mild and fermented well.
-Yes.

185
00:08:31,878 --> 00:08:33,246
This is good.

186
00:08:33,313 --> 00:08:35,815
-But kimchi with vinegar and mustard…
-Yes?

187
00:08:35,949 --> 00:08:37,250
-…will be too sour.
-Right.

188
00:08:37,350 --> 00:08:39,586
-So you normally…
-Yes.

189
00:08:39,719 --> 00:08:41,688
-…dip it in the sauce.
-You change the flavor.

190
00:08:41,755 --> 00:08:43,423
-Wrap it in kimchi.
-I see.

191
00:08:43,556 --> 00:08:45,658
-Then eat it like this.
-Like this?

192
00:08:51,498 --> 00:08:53,633
Korean people like to wrap things.

193
00:08:54,667 --> 00:08:55,869
I guess so.

194
00:09:01,307 --> 00:09:03,576
-We like to wrap everything.
-You do.

195
00:09:08,681 --> 00:09:10,517
-Are these dumplings?
-Yes. Mandu.

196
00:09:10,583 --> 00:09:12,619
Mandu. So it's different from gyoza.

197
00:09:13,420 --> 00:09:15,155
-You dip it in that.
-This one?

198
00:09:15,288 --> 00:09:17,023
I want to try the vinegar and mustard.

199
00:09:21,528 --> 00:09:23,029
-Nice.
-It's delicious.

200
00:09:23,096 --> 00:09:24,864
-It's good.
-I'm glad.

201
00:09:32,439 --> 00:09:34,140
-This sauce goes well with everything.
-Yes.

202
00:09:34,207 --> 00:09:37,243
Vinegar and mustard.
I learned something new today.

203
00:09:41,114 --> 00:09:42,749
-It's good.
-It's delicious.

204
00:09:42,816 --> 00:09:43,817
-Nice.
-Yes.

205
00:09:43,917 --> 00:09:45,985
-You taught me vinegar and mustard.
-Yes.

206
00:09:46,152 --> 00:09:48,688
-So I'll teach you this.
-Yes.

207
00:09:48,822 --> 00:09:50,290
-You eat half the dumpling.
-Yes.

208
00:09:50,423 --> 00:09:52,692
-Then eat the other half with jeyuk.
-Eat it together.

209
00:09:53,226 --> 00:09:55,095
-It's good like this.
-Oh!

210
00:10:01,301 --> 00:10:03,670
You eat it like this.

211
00:10:14,581 --> 00:10:18,451
Eating half the dumpling
with jeyuk and kimchi is really good.

212
00:10:18,585 --> 00:10:20,620
It's like the flavor is multiplying.

213
00:10:20,687 --> 00:10:21,888
It's good.

214
00:10:21,988 --> 00:10:23,156
Yes.

215
00:10:26,593 --> 00:10:28,161
Oh!

216
00:10:28,228 --> 00:10:30,130
You're so into the vinegar
and mustard right now.

217
00:10:30,230 --> 00:10:32,699
-I've never had it before.
-There might be

218
00:10:32,866 --> 00:10:34,734
a revolution in Korea today.

219
00:10:35,235 --> 00:10:37,070
Vinegar and mustard with dumplings.

220
00:10:37,137 --> 00:10:38,171
-Yes.
-Yes.

221
00:10:38,238 --> 00:10:41,241
-By Yutaka Matsushige.
-Yutaka Matsushige. Yes.

222
00:10:41,307 --> 00:10:43,143
Vinegar mustard is the best!

223
00:10:43,243 --> 00:10:45,678
-Oh!
-You can advertise it.

224
00:10:46,012 --> 00:10:48,348
Then only Japanese people
would understand.

225
00:10:48,414 --> 00:10:49,349
That won't do.

226
00:10:53,286 --> 00:10:55,155
-He's really enjoying the dumplings.
-Yes.

227
00:10:55,221 --> 00:10:57,023
-Do you like the dumplings?
-What?

228
00:10:57,123 --> 00:10:58,491
They're delicious.

229
00:10:59,325 --> 00:11:01,161
-It's…
-I'm eating quite a bit today.

230
00:11:01,227 --> 00:11:02,462
I don't know why, though.

231
00:11:06,432 --> 00:11:08,001
I'm really glad.

232
00:11:08,067 --> 00:11:11,604
I'm going to get full
before the cold noodles get here.

233
00:11:11,671 --> 00:11:14,641
But when you have cold noodles,
you have to eat only the cold noodles.

234
00:11:14,707 --> 00:11:15,675
Is that so?

235
00:11:15,742 --> 00:11:18,111
You can't have cold noodles
and dumplings together.

236
00:11:18,178 --> 00:11:20,480
-You have to focus.
-Otherwise, it'll get bloated.

237
00:11:20,547 --> 00:11:21,981
-Oh…
-Yes.

238
00:11:22,115 --> 00:11:24,417
-Shall we have cold noodles now?
-Shall we?

239
00:11:24,484 --> 00:11:26,319
-Okay.
-There are two kinds.

240
00:11:26,386 --> 00:11:29,656
-I recommend the one with the broth.
-Okay.

241
00:11:29,789 --> 00:11:31,558
-One with broth?
-Yes.

