271
00:12:40,960 --> 00:12:43,363
-How do I put this… McDonald's…
-Yes.

272
00:12:43,496 --> 00:12:46,199
Pyeongyang cold noodles are like
handmade burgers. It's different.

273
00:12:46,332 --> 00:12:47,467
-Oh…
-Right.

274
00:12:47,600 --> 00:12:49,235
-Before we eat the noodles…
-Yes?

275
00:12:49,369 --> 00:12:50,870
-…I have to warn you.
-Warn me?

276
00:12:51,004 --> 00:12:53,373
Some people say
Pyeongyang cold noodles are bland.

277
00:12:53,473 --> 00:12:54,941
-When they first try them?
-Yes.

278
00:12:55,008 --> 00:12:57,644
Yes, but I still recommend
you do not add any seasonings.

279
00:13:00,179 --> 00:13:01,047
-It's here.
-It's here.

280
00:13:01,114 --> 00:13:02,248
-It's here.
-Yes.

281
00:13:06,986 --> 00:13:11,958
COLD NOODLES WITH BROTH: 15,000 WON
APPROXIMATELY 1,500 YEN

282
00:13:12,091 --> 00:13:15,862
-They mix meat broth…
-Yes.

283
00:13:15,928 --> 00:13:19,799
-…and kimchi broth.
-Wow.

284
00:13:20,333 --> 00:13:23,202
-It looks completely different.
-Yes.

285
00:13:23,336 --> 00:13:24,837
-You can have it like this.
-Right.

286
00:13:24,937 --> 00:13:27,940
-Try the broth first.
-Broth first?

287
00:13:28,074 --> 00:13:29,642
-Drink it just like this?
-Yes, the spoon…

288
00:13:29,709 --> 00:13:31,944
They don't have spoons here.

289
00:13:32,078 --> 00:13:33,446
They don't?

290
00:13:33,613 --> 00:13:34,781
SI-KYUNG'S WAY OF EATING

291
00:13:34,847 --> 00:13:36,983
STEP ONE, DRINK THE BROTH FIRST

292
00:13:38,451 --> 00:13:39,752
Wow…

293
00:13:53,833 --> 00:13:55,101
Wow.

294
00:13:56,202 --> 00:13:58,404
The flavor is so deep.

295
00:13:58,938 --> 00:14:02,141
-Then you mix the noodles.
-Yes.

296
00:14:02,241 --> 00:14:04,110
-This is amazing.
-Yes.

297
00:14:05,278 --> 00:14:07,480
-Then you go like this.
-Yes.

298
00:14:08,147 --> 00:14:13,886
The noodles are quite long.

299
00:14:24,831 --> 00:14:26,366
It's delicate.

300
00:14:26,532 --> 00:14:30,870
I can see why some people
might think it's bland.

301
00:14:31,003 --> 00:14:32,038
Yes.

302
00:14:50,289 --> 00:14:52,992
It is hard

303
00:14:53,826 --> 00:14:56,295
to describe the flavor of the broth.

304
00:14:58,030 --> 00:15:02,869
There is a deep flavor in the broth.

305
00:15:02,969 --> 00:15:04,771
-Right. It's just as you said.
-Right?

306
00:15:04,837 --> 00:15:07,540
It's nice to savor the taste as I eat it.

307
00:15:08,307 --> 00:15:09,842
-A chef once said this.
-Yes?

308
00:15:09,909 --> 00:15:13,312
Normally, when you taste something
you can immediately tell

309
00:15:13,379 --> 00:15:16,182
-if it's sweet, spicy, or salty.
-Yes.

310
00:15:16,249 --> 00:15:17,984
-It's easy to distinguish the flavor.
-Yes.

311
00:15:18,117 --> 00:15:21,354
But this is the kind of dish
where you explore

312
00:15:21,487 --> 00:15:23,756
-and discover the flavor yourself.
-Yes.

313
00:15:23,823 --> 00:15:27,460
-That's why it’s a true gourmet food.
-Right.

314
00:15:27,560 --> 00:15:30,530
It's unlike any cold noodles
I've ever had before.

315
00:15:30,630 --> 00:15:35,368
So most people don't say,

316
00:15:35,435 --> 00:15:36,769
"What is this? It's good!"

317
00:15:36,836 --> 00:15:37,937
-right away.
-Yes.

318
00:15:38,037 --> 00:15:41,174
-They go, "What is this?"
-Gradually.

319
00:15:41,274 --> 00:15:43,643
-"This is new. It's interesting."
-Yes.

320
00:15:43,776 --> 00:15:46,345
-"It's deep. I'm not so sure about it."
-Yes.

321
00:15:46,412 --> 00:15:48,247
-But if you come here 10 times…
-Yes.

322
00:15:48,314 --> 00:15:50,550
-…it becomes really addictive.
-Right.

323
00:15:50,650 --> 00:15:52,018
I get it.

324
00:15:57,557 --> 00:16:00,293
So this is what
little Si-kyung got addicted to.

325
00:16:00,393 --> 00:16:02,028
-Yes.
-When you were young.

326
00:16:02,094 --> 00:16:03,262
Yes.

327
00:16:08,901 --> 00:16:11,671
-I think that will happen to me too.
-Wow.

328
00:16:12,338 --> 00:16:15,007
-It's delicious.
-I'm happy.

329
00:16:15,107 --> 00:16:17,310
In Korea, there’s
the “Three Great Cold Noodles.”

330
00:16:17,376 --> 00:16:18,845
Jinju cold noodles from Jinju.

331
00:16:18,978 --> 00:16:19,979
-It's in the south.
-Yes.

332
00:16:20,146 --> 00:16:22,148
-Since it's in the south near the ocean…
-Yes.

333
00:16:22,215 --> 00:16:25,451
-…they use seafood for the broth.
-The broth is different.

334
00:16:25,585 --> 00:16:26,819
-Right.
-Oh…

335
00:16:26,886 --> 00:16:27,787
Hamhung cold noodles.

336
00:16:27,854 --> 00:16:29,989
Hamhung is in North Korea.

337
00:16:30,089 --> 00:16:31,824
They add potato starch to the noodles.

338
00:16:31,891 --> 00:16:34,627
-It makes it very chewy.
-Wow…

339
00:16:34,760 --> 00:16:36,529
And here they have
Pyeongyang Cold Noodles.

340
00:16:36,596 --> 00:16:38,264
-Pyeongyang Cold Noodles.
-Yes.

341
00:16:39,298 --> 00:16:41,801
How do you add more flavor to this?

342
00:16:42,502 --> 00:16:45,838
-You can add some chili powder.
-This?

343
00:16:46,739 --> 00:16:48,774
-It smells nice.
-It changes the flavor.

344
00:16:48,841 --> 00:16:50,109
That's perfect.

345
00:16:50,176 --> 00:16:53,079
SI-KYUNG'S WAY OF EATING
STEP TWO, ADD CHILI POWDER

346
00:17:10,663 --> 00:17:12,865
The noodles,
which seemed expressionless at first,

347
00:17:12,932 --> 00:17:16,002
slowly change as they absorb the broth.

348
00:17:16,102 --> 00:17:18,337
-Oh, that's very poetic.
-Yes.

349
00:17:18,471 --> 00:17:21,607
You gave life to the noodles.

350
00:17:21,674 --> 00:17:24,010
Well, noodles are awesome.

351
00:17:30,983 --> 00:17:33,219
-Wow.
-There's another way to change it.

352
00:17:33,386 --> 00:17:37,557
-Yes?
-You crush the boiled egg yolk.

353
00:17:37,623 --> 00:17:39,959
-It changes the broth again.
-Yes.

354
00:17:40,493 --> 00:17:43,162
SI-KYUNG'S WAY OF EATING
