368
00:18:26,772 --> 00:18:28,474
He had one more dumpling than me.

369
00:18:29,108 --> 00:18:30,543
-Are you okay?
-What do you mean?

370
00:18:30,610 --> 00:18:32,712
Aren't you eating too much?
Will you be okay?

371
00:18:32,812 --> 00:18:35,815
-I have quite the appetite today.
-Oh…

372
00:18:35,915 --> 00:18:37,416
Is it because it's good?

373
00:18:39,185 --> 00:18:43,789
-My parents are quite old now.
-Yes.

374
00:18:43,923 --> 00:18:45,691
-But they can finish the whole bowl.
-Really?

375
00:18:45,825 --> 00:18:48,461
-How old are they?
-They are…

376
00:18:48,561 --> 00:18:52,999
-They were born in 1945, 46.
-So almost 80.

377
00:18:53,132 --> 00:18:54,266
-Right.
-Yes.

378
00:18:54,367 --> 00:18:56,168
-They're 80 this year.
-Yes.

379
00:18:56,302 --> 00:18:57,470
-I just remembered…
-Yes?

380
00:18:57,536 --> 00:18:59,805
In Japan, we talked about

381
00:18:59,872 --> 00:19:01,741
-what it is to be a gourmet.
-Yes.

382
00:19:01,874 --> 00:19:04,710
But you seem to have a curiosity

383
00:19:04,777 --> 00:19:07,880
about different flavors.

384
00:19:07,980 --> 00:19:12,351
-You don't accept the flavor as it is.
-Yes.

385
00:19:12,451 --> 00:19:14,987
-You keep thinking about…
-Yes.

386
00:19:15,054 --> 00:19:16,989
…adding seasonings
and changing the flavor.

387
00:19:17,123 --> 00:19:18,691
-You are a gourmet.
-Yes.

388
00:19:18,824 --> 00:19:21,394
But some gourmets
don’t hesitate to spend big

389
00:19:21,494 --> 00:19:25,297
when it comes to good food.

390
00:19:25,364 --> 00:19:27,533
-Yes.
-They spend a lot of money…

391
00:19:27,600 --> 00:19:29,168
-Yes.
-…on fine dining.

392
00:19:29,335 --> 00:19:32,171
-I'm not like that.
-Me either.

393
00:19:32,238 --> 00:19:37,343
I want to understand
what makes a certain flavor

394
00:19:37,443 --> 00:19:41,047
so beloved by locals for decades.

395
00:19:41,113 --> 00:19:44,083
I think that's what being a gourmet is.
So I want to ask,

396
00:19:44,216 --> 00:19:48,120
what is it about the flavor
of these noodles

397
00:19:48,187 --> 00:19:50,256
-that makes them so loved by locals…
-Yes.

398
00:19:50,356 --> 00:19:53,125
…including you and your parents,

399
00:19:53,192 --> 00:19:55,594
for the past 40 years?

400
00:19:55,661 --> 00:19:58,597
Knowing the answer to that question
is the happiness

401
00:19:58,664 --> 00:20:01,133
-that comes from good food.
-Oh…

402
00:20:01,200 --> 00:20:02,568
-It's just like you said.
-It's memorable.

403
00:20:02,635 --> 00:20:03,669
-Yes.
-Oh.

404
00:20:03,769 --> 00:20:08,007
If those who enjoy doing that
are called gourmets,

405
00:20:08,107 --> 00:20:11,143
I think I would like to be called one.

406
00:20:11,210 --> 00:20:12,211
Right.

407
00:20:14,113 --> 00:20:16,015
I could eat some more.

