431
00:21:47,406 --> 00:21:49,008
…but fall in love with Pyeongyang ones.

432
00:21:49,074 --> 00:21:50,176
Right.

433
00:21:57,016 --> 00:21:58,717
-Then you wrap this…
-Yes.

434
00:21:58,784 --> 00:21:59,885
We keep wrapping food.

435
00:21:59,952 --> 00:22:02,321
-You do like wrapping food.
-Yes.

436
00:22:02,388 --> 00:22:05,124
-We want to wrap everything.
-Go ahead.

437
00:22:07,593 --> 00:22:08,494
Oh.

438
00:22:13,032 --> 00:22:14,500
Oh, I'm full.

439
00:22:14,567 --> 00:22:15,868
-Yes.
-Right.

440
00:22:17,603 --> 00:22:20,506
-Are you full right now?
-I am so full.

441
00:22:20,639 --> 00:22:23,642
Just like earlier today,
it’s surprisingly easy to digest.

442
00:22:23,709 --> 00:22:24,977
Maybe it's because it's so good.

443
00:22:25,544 --> 00:22:27,613
-You digest quickly if the food is good?
-Yes.

444
00:22:28,514 --> 00:22:30,649
-I've never heard that before.
-For real.

445
00:22:30,749 --> 00:22:33,552
-That is a new theory.
-When it’s really good,

446
00:22:33,686 --> 00:22:35,487
it feels like your body just kicks out

447
00:22:35,554 --> 00:22:37,189
